node.text: It’s very tempting in our culture to find a woman every few years who becomes the receptacle for our fear,envy,disapprobation and hatred. There’s nothing like a young,inscrutably famous woman who we do not know personally , for attracting the projection of our basest shadow. Whether it’s Marilyn Monroe,Princess Diana,Monica Lewinsky,Britney Spears,Caroline Flack or the countless others that are destroyed or almost destroyed, this hurts ALL of us . It’s almost impossible to form a considered opinion of any person without knowing them personally;and yet we are flooded with how to receive these women, their success,their bodies,their sexuality,perceived greed,ambition and assumed morality with piecemeal or completely skewed information pouring at us. I have almost no interest in the Royal Family but I am very grateful to @archiemannersmagic and @joshua_pieters for illustrating how keen these experts are to form and disseminate their largely negative opinions TWO days before the interview is even aired. Piling on a young,pregnant woman of color and shitting all over everything she has said before she has even said it doesn’t just hurt her. It hurts all of us, giving rein to the desire to reduce and destroy and burn witches. Watch the interview or don’t, I couldn’t give a flying bugger.But remember that knee jerk glee at destroying a woman you don’t know is not only of your choosing. We like to destroy powerful young women through OUR OWN fear. Be brave x
